<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A man has been accused of indecently photographing a little girl while she was shopping at Bunnings with her family. </p>

<p>The eight-year-old girl visited the North Mackay store in Queensland on Saturday September 5. </p>

<p>Police allege the 25-year-old man took pictures of the girl while she browsed the warehouse with her family. </p>

<p>Detectives from the Mackay Child Protection and Investigation Unit arrested the man at his Ball Bay home.</p>

<p>They searched the property and allegedly found several images of other girls at the store on a mobile phone. </p>

<p>The alleged victims are yet to be identified.  </p>

<p>More to come </p>

